# About Me

I'm Jared Stewart, a software engineer and technical leader passionate about building scalable systems and leading high-performing engineering teams.

## Professional Background

With years of experience in software development, I've worked across various technologies and domains, from early-stage startups to established companies. I enjoy the intersection of technical excellence and team leadership, focusing on:

- Building scalable, maintainable software systems
- Leading and mentoring engineering teams
- Solving complex technical challenges
- Fostering collaborative development cultures

## Interests

Beyond professional work, I'm interested in:

- Open source contributions
- Technical writing and knowledge sharing
- Continuous learning and skill development
- The evolving landscape of software engineering

## Connect

Feel free to reach out if you'd like to discuss technology, potential collaborations, or just connect with a fellow engineer. You can find me on [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/jaredandrewstewart/) or [GitHub](https://github.com/JaredStewart).

For a more formal overview of my experience, check out my [obligatory resume](/resume).